ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A HealthMap of Romania can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4808554,122.

Measles is a highly contagious, serious disease caused by a virus. In 1980, before widespread vaccination, measles caused an estimated 2.6 million deaths each year. The key facts regarding measles are:

- Measles is one of the leading causes of death among young children even though a safe and cost-effective vaccine is available.
- In 2015, there were 134 200 measles deaths globally, about 367 deaths every day or 15 deaths every hour.
- Measles vaccination resulted in a 79% drop in measles deaths between 2000 and 2015 worldwide.
- In 2015, about 85% of the world's children received one dose of measles vaccine by their 1st birthday through routine health services, up from 73% in 2000.
- During 2000-2015, measles vaccination prevented an estimated 20.3 million deaths, making measles vaccine one of the best buys in public health.
Excerpted from: http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs286/en/. - Mod.LK]
